parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the lambda sensor can cause the engine control unit to malfunction, leading to incorrect fuel mixture, which can result in unburned fuel igniting in the exhaust, potentially causing a fire.
The failure of the fuel injector fuse can cause the engine to stall or die while in motion, leading to a loss of control and potential accidents.

The failure of the radiator can cause coolant loss, leading to overheating, engine damage, and potential fires. The steam released can also obstruct the driver's vision, increasing the risk of accidents.
The failure of the catalytic converter can cause the engine to malfunction, leading to poor performance, decreased fuel efficiency, and potential environmental hazards.
A malfunctioning seatbelt buckle or latch can prevent the seatbelt from properly securing the passenger, increasing the risk of injury or fatality in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seatbelt buckle is stuck in a depressed position
the seatbelt latch will not lock
the seatbelt buckle does not spring back into place
the seatbelt latch becomes continuously depressed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning cruise control can cause the vehicle to accelerate rapidly and uncontrollably, leading to potential accidents, loss of control, and rear-end collisions.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates rapidly and uncontrollably when cruise control is activated
and lurches; the vehicle overcompensates in speed fluctuations
causing sudden and extreme speed increases; the accelerator pedal feels stuck
causing the vehicle to reach dangerous speeds in a short time.
